{%- style -%}
  .advertorial {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .advertorial h1, .advertorial h2, .advertorial h3 {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .advertorial-wrapper {
    max-width: 1240px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 20px;
  }
  .advertorial-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 8fr 4fr;
    gap: 30px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .advertorial-article {
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .advertorial-article h1 {
    font-size: 40px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .advertorial-article .article-date {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .advertorial .pull-quote {
    background: #EBFEFB;
    padding: 16px 16px 16px 24px;
    border-left: 4px solid #339B43;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 24px 0;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
  }
  .advertorial .article-img {
    border-radius: 16px;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 24px 0;
  }
  .advertorial .article-img.rounded-32 {
    border-radius: 32px;
  }
  .advertorial .sub-heading {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
  }
  .advertorial .stat-callout {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #dd1d1d;
    margin: 20px 0;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: #fff5f5;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .advertorial .cta-box {
    background: #f0fdf4;
    border: 2px solid #339B43;
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 28px 24px;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }
  .advertorial .cta-box p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .advertorial .cta-button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    background: #2D5F3F;
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 16px 32px;
    border-radius: 32px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .advertorial .cta-button:hover {
    background: #339B43;
  }
  .advertorial .cta-button svg {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .advertorial .testimonial {
    background: #f9fafb;
    border-left: 4px solid #339B43;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .advertorial .testimonial .author {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #2D5F3F;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  .advertorial .feature-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 16px 0;
  }
  .advertorial .feature-list li {
    padding: 8px 0;
    padding-left: 28px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .advertorial .feature-list li::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #339B43;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 18px;
  }
  .advertorial .feature-list li strong {
    color: #1a1a1a;
  }
  .advertorial .video-wrapper {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    padding-bottom: 56.25%;
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 24px 0;
    background: #000;
  }
  .advertorial .video-wrapper iframe {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
  }
  .advertorial .video-thumbnail {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .advertorial .video-play-btn {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    width: 68px;
    height: 68px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .advertorial .video-play-btn:hover {
    background: #ef0800;
  }
  .advertorial .video-play-btn svg {
    width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
    margin-left: 4px;
  }
  /* Sidebar */
  .advertorial-sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 32px;
  }
  .advertorial .sidebar-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    border-radius: 24px;
    padding: 24px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .advertorial .sidebar-card .product-img {
    width: 40%;
    margin: 0 auto 12px;
    display: block;
  }
  .advertorial .sidebar-card .stars {
    color: #FDAC2B;
    font-size: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .advertorial .sidebar-card .rating-text {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .advertorial .sidebar-card .sidebar-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
  }
  .advertorial .sidebar-card .sidebar-photo {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .advertorial .sidebar-card .sidebar-sub {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  /* Green banner */
  .advertorial-banner {
    background: #2D5F3F;
    padding: 16px 0;
  }
  .advertorial-banner img {
    width: 25%;
    max-width: 149px;
    display: block;
  }
  .advertorial-banner .banner-inner {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  /* Guarantee badge */
  .advertorial .guarantee-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #f0fdf4;
    border: 2px solid #339B43;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 8px 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2D5F3F;
    margin: 12px 0;
  }
  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .advertorial-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .advertorial-article h1 {
      font-size: 30px;
    }
    .advertorial {
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .advertorial .sub-heading {
      font-size: 20px;
    }
    .advertorial-sidebar {
      position: static;
      order: -1;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .advertorial-banner .banner-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .advertorial-banner img {
      width: 50%;
    }
    .advertorial .cta-button {
      font-size: 16px;
      padding: 14px 24px;
    }
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1024px) {
    .advertorial-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .advertorial-sidebar {
      position: static;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
  }
{%- endstyle -%}

{%- assign cta_url = section.settings.cta_url -%}
{%- assign cta_text = section.settings.cta_text -%}
{%- assign sidebar_cta_text = section.settings.sidebar_cta_text -%}

<section class="advertorial">
  <!-- Green Banner -->
  <div class="advertorial-banner">
    <div class="banner-inner">
      <a href="{{ cta_url }}" title="Waggier">
        <img src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-f16b6ad4-a54f-4746-8c4e-82ed9f484654.png?v=14875919882035262134" alt="Waggier" loading="eager" width="149" height="51">
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Content Grid -->
  <div class="advertorial-wrapper">
    <div class="advertorial-grid">

      <!-- LEFT COLUMN: Article -->
      <div class="advertorial-article">
        <h1>Dog Owner Exposes Hidden Truth: The 30-Minute Timer That Nearly Killed Her Corgi</h1>
        <p class="article-date">August 05 2025 at 9:17 AM PST</p>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          "My vet circled the timer on the wall: 'If your dog's stomach flips, you have 30 minutes or she dies.'"
        </div>

        <img class="article-img" src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-18501f23-4284-41f3-a748-fc95e99157ac.jpg?v=4993775241241843745" alt="Dog eating" loading="eager" width="748" height="416">

        <p><strong>I thought Sophie just loved her food.</strong></p>

        <p>Turns out I'd been playing Russian roulette with her life twice a day for three years.</p>
        <p>If your dog wolfs down their meals in under 60 seconds...</p>
        <p>If you've ever joked about them being a "vacuum cleaner" at dinner time...</p>
        <p>If you think fast eating is just enthusiasm for food...</p>
        <p><strong>Then what I'm about to share could save your dog's life.</strong></p>

        <div class="stat-callout">
          Every single day, 30% of dogs who develop bloat die -- even WITH emergency treatment.
        </div>

        <img class="article-img" src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-f3d242cb-53cb-4379-b5ee-de99ffa52915.jpg?v=7711609496902943307" alt="Dog with food" loading="eager" width="748" height="511">

        <p>And here's the terrifying part: The "enthusiastic eating" you laugh about is actually filling your dog's stomach with invisible air bombs that can detonate 20 minutes after any meal.</p>
        <p>I'm talking about something vets call <strong>GDV</strong> -- Gastric Dilatation Volvulus.</p>
        <p>But this isn't the obvious emergency you can see coming.</p>
        <p>This is the silent killer that strikes during a normal Tuesday dinner... then gives you exactly 30 minutes to save your dog's life.</p>

        <!-- The Night Everything Changed -->
        <h2 class="sub-heading">The Night Everything Changed</h2>

        <p>My name is Jennifer Thompson.</p>
        <p>Three years ago, I thought I was a responsible dog owner.</p>
        <p>I live in Denver with my husband Mark and our Corgi Sophie. Premium food. Regular vet visits. Daily walks. I did everything right.</p>
        <p>Or so I thought...</p>
        <p>Sophie had always wolfed down her food -- 60 seconds flat for a whole bowl. We used to post videos of her "eating performances" that friends found hilarious.</p>
        <p>"Look at her go! She must really love that salmon recipe!"</p>
        <p>That Tuesday started like any other dinner time.</p>
        <p>Sophie inhaled her kibble as usual. I cleaned her bowl while she wandered to her bed.</p>
        <p>Twenty minutes later, I heard a sound I'll never forget.</p>
        <p>Not quite a whine. Not quite a retch. Something guttural and wrong.</p>
        <p>Sophie was standing in the hallway, sides heaving, trying to vomit but nothing coming up.</p>
        <p>Just foam. White foam and desperate gulping sounds.</p>

        <img class="article-img" src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-006dd5d4-3e9b-460e-b7b6-8aa6bc738940.jpg?v=15898945611377956177" alt="Dog in distress" loading="lazy" width="748" height="374">

        <p>Her stomach looked different. Swollen. Tight like a basketball.</p>
        <p>"Mark, something's wrong with Sophie!"</p>
        <p>She couldn't sit. Couldn't lie down. Just stood there, head hanging, drooling strings of foam.</p>
        <p>I called our vet's emergency line. The tech's voice changed instantly.</p>
        <p>"Get her here immediately. Don't wait. Drive fast but safe."</p>
        <p>The panic in her voice told me everything.</p>

        <!-- The Race Against Time -->
        <h2 class="sub-heading">The Race Against Time</h2>

        <p>During that endless 12-minute drive, Sophie's breathing got shallower. The foam turned pink-tinged.</p>
        <p>The vet tech was waiting in the parking lot with a gurney. No paperwork. No questions. Just movement.</p>
        <p>Dr. Martinez appeared in surgical scrubs.</p>
        <p>"Sophie has GDV. Her stomach has flipped and is cutting off blood supply. We need to operate immediately."</p>
        <p>"Is she going to --"</p>
        <p>"We have maybe 20 minutes before tissue starts dying. I need your consent now."</p>

        <div class="stat-callout">
          $4,800. Four hours of surgery. One blood transfusion.
        </div>

        <img class="article-img" src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-128f3ef8-b8b8-4e5e-aa75-424d668d58e3.jpg?v=4970736308018695682" alt="Veterinary care" loading="lazy" width="748" height="512">

        <p><strong>Sophie survived.</strong></p>
        <p>Barely.</p>

        <!-- The Shocking Truth -->
        <h2 class="sub-heading">The Shocking Truth Nobody Tells You</h2>

        <p>At 3 AM, while Sophie recovered, Dr. Martinez sat with me.</p>
        <p>"This wasn't bad luck," she said. "Fast eating causes dogs to swallow massive amounts of air. That air creates a gas bubble that can flip the stomach at any time."</p>
        <p>"But lots of dogs eat fast --"</p>
        <p>"And GDV kills more of them than cancer. The difference is cancer takes months. GDV takes minutes."</p>
        <p>She pulled up Sophie's x-rays.</p>
        <p>"See this dark area? That's all the air she swallowed. Every fast meal creates this bomb in their stomach."</p>

        <img class="article-img" src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-0bbe880e-2af7-4ea7-9b9b-813d1b551b51.jpg?v=8250532506872505487" alt="X-ray showing air in stomach" loading="lazy" width="748" height="615">

        <p>I thought about every meal Sophie had ever eaten. Hundreds of invisible dice rolls.</p>
        <p>"We tried tennis balls in her bowl," I said weakly.</p>
        <p>Dr. Martinez shook her head.</p>
        <p>"Tennis balls just make them eat around obstacles while still gulping air. The real problem is neurological."</p>

        <!-- The Hidden Trigger -->
        <h2 class="sub-heading">The Hidden Trigger Your Vet Never Mentioned</h2>

        <p>"Your dog's brain can't tell the difference between eating at home and competing for a carcass in the wild," she explained.</p>
        <p>"When food is presented in a pile -- ANY pile -- it triggers their competitive feeding instinct. They're not eating fast because they're hungry. They're eating fast because their brain thinks another wolf might steal their food."</p>
        <p>She showed me a study from the Journal of Veterinary Behavior.</p>

        <div class="stat-callout">
          Traditional slow feeders reduced eating speed by 40% but only reduced air intake by 10%.
        </div>

        <p>"Speed isn't the enemy. Air is. And air comes from the gulping motion triggered by competitive feeding response."</p>
        <p>All those solutions I'd tried? They slowed the eating but didn't stop the air gulping because the competitive trigger was still firing.</p>

        <!-- The Discovery -->
        <h2 class="sub-heading">The Discovery That Changed Everything</h2>

        <p>Three days later, I brought Sophie home with 14 inches of incision staples.</p>
        <p>That's when my neighbor Sarah stopped by. Her German Shepherd had bloated twice. $12,000 total.</p>
        <p>"After the second surgery, our emergency vet told me about something that actually addresses the trigger," she said.</p>
        <p>She showed me a video on her phone. Her dog eating calmly, methodically, no gulping motions.</p>
        <p>"It's called the PaceBowl. The honeycomb design doesn't just create obstacles -- it breaks up the food so dramatically that the brain stops seeing it as one resource to defend."</p>
        <p>"Watch his neck. See? No lurching gulp. His brain switched from 'compete' to 'explore.' No competitive response means no air gulping."</p>
        <p>"Eight months since we switched. Zero bloat scares."</p>

        <img class="article-img rounded-32" src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-8ea82762-ec6a-4899-af0f-cab4da319c89.jpg?v=11330563332805728809" alt="PaceBowl" loading="lazy" width="748" height="748">

        <!-- The Solution -->
        <h2 class="sub-heading">The Solution That Actually Works</h2>

        <p>I ordered the <a href="{{ cta_url }}">Waggier PaceBowl</a> that afternoon.</p>
        <p>When it arrived, I was skeptical. Another "miracle" solution.</p>
        <p>But Sophie's reaction was immediate and bizarre.</p>
        <p>Instead of her usual frantic gulping, she paused. Sniffed. Started eating with careful, exploring movements.</p>
        <p>No neck lurching. No desperate gulps. Just steady, calm eating.</p>
        <p>The meal that used to take 60 seconds took 10 minutes.</p>
        <p>But here's what shocked me: I could HEAR the difference.</p>
        <p>Before: <em>Gulp-gulp-gulp-gulp.</em></p>
        <p>Now: <em>Crunch... crunch... explore... crunch.</em></p>
        <p>No air rushing. No panic. Just eating.</p>

        <!-- Video Embed -->
        <div class="video-wrapper" data-vimeo-id="1109612615">
          <img class="video-thumbnail" src="//waggier.com/cdn/shop/files/gempages_579706557655155460-c9da892a-bf6a-4802-bae0-330e9ae1d851.jpg?v=4042919175429110516" alt="PaceBowl video" loading="eager" width="748" height="421">
